  RELEVANCE: Rupert's systems-based critique provides an alternative framework for individuating cognitive systems that competes with the functionalist approach underlying EMT. His emphasis on empirical evidence and explanatory adequacy connects theoretical debates to actual cognitive scientific practice. The portability and reliability arguments bear directly on when external resources can function as genuine cognitive components in offloading scenarios.

  POSITION: Systems-based internalist critique emphasizing empirical adequacy and explanatory boundaries.
  },
