  RELEVANCE: Wheeler provides the most sophisticated defense of the compatibility between functionalism and parity. His account of appropriate functional equivalence refines what parity demands, addressing grain-of-realization worries. Essential for understanding how parity-based arguments can respond to internalist critiques while maintaining functionalist commitments.

  POSITION: Pro-parity functionalist. Defends parity as compatible with properly understood functionalism.
