  RELEVANCE: Smithies provides an epistemological rather than metaphysical critique of parity. The access-based argument challenges whether functionally equivalent internal and external states provide the same epistemic support for belief. This matters for cognitive offloading: even if external tools play equivalent functional roles, they may not provide equivalent epistemic access, undermining parity from an internalist epistemological perspective.

